From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Subject: [PATCH] test/crimson: bump unittest-seastar-messenger-thrash --memory to 1G

unittest-seastar-messenger-thrash runs with `--memory 256M --smp 1`, which
is just enough for upstream x86_64 CI but too tight on riscv64: the test
runs on seastar's per-shard allocator, hits the strict 256M cap mid-run,
and aborts with:

  Reactor stalled for 66 ms on shard 0, in scheduling group main.
  Reactor stalled for 124 ms on shard 0, in scheduling group main.
  ERROR ... test - Test failed: got exception
    ceph::buffer::v15_2_0::bad_alloc (Bad allocation [buffer:1])

Bumping the budget to 1G lets the test run to completion on riscv64
(97 sec wall on sg2044).  The sister test unittest-seastar-messenger keeps
the upstream 256M --smp 4 invocation since it passes unchanged.

This is environment-specific tuning rather than a bug fix, so the bump is
not proposed upstream.

---
 src/test/crimson/CMakeLists.txt | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/test/crimson/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/test/crimson/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -92,7 +92,7 @@

 add_executable(unittest-seastar-messenger-thrash test_messenger_thrash.cc)
 add_ceph_unittest(unittest-seastar-messenger-thrash
-  --memory 256M --smp 1)
+  --memory 1G --smp 1)
 target_link_libraries(unittest-seastar-messenger-thrash crimson)

 add_subdirectory(seastore)
